pageContext.claim: “Very soon you're going to get to 355 beautiful ships. 355.”
pageContext.analysis: The Navy, which now has 283 ships, announced the 355-ship goal in December, 2016, before Trump became president. Under no definition would that total be reached "very soon." The current plan calls for that number to be reached in the 2050s, though under a robust ship-building plan it could be reached by the 2030, the Navy said.
